value.value: Solid sterile single-dose preparation consisting of a strip made of a suitable material usually impregnated with active substance(s) intended for use on the eyeball.
Administration device for administering a liquid or semi-solid pharmaceutical form to the oral cavity.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for oral use. The preparation is administered in small volumes as drops by means of a suitable device such as a dropper. The measured dose may be diluted in water or another suitable liquid before swallowing.

label.value: Oral Drops, Granules for Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of granules intended to be dissolved in the specified liquid to obtain an oral drops solution.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a liquid active substance per se, intended for oral use. The preparation is administered in small volumes as drops by means of a suitable device such as a dropper. The measured dose may be diluted in water or another suitable liquid before swallowing.

label.value: Oral Drops, Powder for Suspension Dosage Form

value.value: Solid preparation consisting of one or more powders intended to be dispersed in the specified liquid to obtain an oral drops suspension.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a solution intended for oral use. The preparation is administered in small volumes as drops by means of a suitable device such as a dropper. The measured dose may be diluted in water or another suitable liquid before swallowing.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a suspension intended for oral use. The preparation is administered in small volumes as drops by means of a suitable device such as a dropper. The measured dose may be diluted in water or another suitable liquid before swallowing.

Liquid, single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for oral use. Each dose from a multidose container is administered by means of a device suitable for measuring the prescribed volume. The device is usually a spoon or a cup for volumes of 5 mL or multiples thereof or an oral syringe for other volumes.

label.value: Oral Emulsion in Sachet Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an oral emulsion presented in a sachet.

Solid preparation consisting of whole, broken or fragmented plants or parts of plants in an unprocessed state (herbal drug), intended for oral use without requiring transformation (e.g. dissolution or dispersion in water); the material may be dried or fresh, and may be chewed before being swallowed. The word 'plant' is used in the broader sense to include also algae, fungi and lichens.

Liquid, single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of a liquid active substance per se, intended for oral use. Each dose from a multidose container is administered by means of a device suitable for measuring the prescribed volume. The device is usually a spoon or a cup for volumes of 5 mL or multiples thereof or an oral syringe for other volumes.

Solid single-dose preparation made by freeze-drying of a liquid or semi-solid preparation. This fast-releasing preparation is intended to be placed in the mouth where its contents are released in saliva and swallowed or, alternatively, to be dissolved in water before oral administration.

label.value: Oral Paste in Sachet Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an oral paste presented in a sachet.

label.value: Oral Powder in Sachet Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an oral powder presented in a sachet.

label.value: Oral Solution in Sachet Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an oral solution presented in a sachet.

label.value: Oral Solution in Single-dose Container Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an oral solution presented in a single-dose container.

label.value: Oral Solution/Concentrate for Nebulizer Solution Dosage Form

value.value: Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for oral use or intended to be diluted in the specified liquid to obtain a nebulizer solution.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation for veterinary use consisting of a suspension intended for oral use. It is administered by spraying, including by spraying as coarse droplets over the animal(s), which then consume the product, for example during preening.

label.value: Oral Suspension in Pre-filled Oral Applicator Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an oral suspension presented in a pre-filled oral applicator.

label.value: Oral Suspension in Sachet Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an oral suspension presented in a sachet.
Administration device for administering a liquid or semi-solid pharmaceutical form to the oral cavity.
Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for oral or rectal use.
Liquid preparation consisting of a suspension intended for oral or rectal use.
Solid preparation consisting of a single- or multilayer sheet of suitable material(s) intended to be placed in the mouth where it disperses rapidly before being swallowed.
The technique of administration of a pharmaceutical product by placing it in the mouth and allowing it to dissipate; the product is usually then swallowed.

Relating to the mouth as the intended site of administration, where the pharmaceutical product is administered with the intention of acting on the mucosa of the mouth, whether for local or systemic use.
Solid single-dose preparation contained in a soft shell to be chewed or sucked to obtain a local effect in the oral cavity.

Semi-solid, usually multidose preparation consisting of an oil-in-water emulsion intended for oromucosal use. Oromucosal creams are applied to the oral cavity or onto a specific part of the oral cavity, other than the gingivae, to obtain a local effect.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a solution, suspension or emulsion intended for oromucosal use. Oromucosal drops are administered by instillation into the oral cavity or onto a specific part of the oral cavity.

Semi-solid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of a hydrophilic gel intended for oromucosal use. It is applied to the oral cavity or onto a specific part of the oral cavity, to obtain a local effect.
Semi-solid multidose preparation consisting of an ointment intended for oromucosal use. It is applied to the oral cavity or onto a specific part of the oral cavity, to obtain a local effect

Semi-solid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of a paste of solid particles finely dispersed in a hydrophilic basis intended for oromucosal use. Oromucosal pastes are applied to the oral cavity or onto a specific part of the oral cavity, to obtain a local effect.

Flexible single-dose preparation intended to be applied to the oral cavity to obtain either a systemic or a local effect by delivering the active substance(s) over a certain period of time, after which it is then removed.

label.value: Oromucosal Powder in Pouch Dosage Form

value.value: Medicinal product consisting of an oromucosal powder presented in a pouch.

label.value: Albino Stock, Pet Shop, Birmingham, AL 1958

value.value: Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of a solution intended for oromucosal use.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of an emulsion intended for oromucosal use. It is administered by spraying into the oral cavity or onto a specific part of the oral cavity or the throat. It is presented in a container with a spray pump or in a pressurized container with or without a metering valve.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a solution intended for oromucosal use. It is administered by spraying into the oral cavity or onto a specific part of the oral cavity or the throat. It is presented in a container with a spray pump or in a pressurized container with or without a metering valve.

Liquid, usually multidose preparation consisting of a suspension intended for oromucosal use. It is administered by spraying into the oral cavity or onto a specific part of the oral cavity or the throat. It is presented in a container with a spray pump or in a pressurized container with or without a metering valve.
Liquid single-dose or multidose preparation consisting of a suspension intended for oromucosal use.
Liquid preparation consisting of a solution intended for oromucosal or laryngopharyngeal use.
A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single discrete entity where the pharmaceutical dose form is a type of pastille.
A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single pen container.
A unit of presentation used to represent the quantity of product that is found in a single discrete entity where the pharmaceutical dose form is a type of pendant.
Semi-solid preparation consisting of a gel intended to be placed in the pouch between the tooth and the gingiva.
